reviewtext: We bought two of these, basically because they were the cheapest 7 foot cable I could find on Amazon.  We've got other Belkin equipment, and have been happy with it.  But, to be honest I didn't expect much for that price.  I figured it would be cheaply made, toothpick size cable, or the end locks would break right away.  They were actually a pleasant surprise, especially for how cheap they were being sold.  Can't complain a bit.
summary: A nice, thick, pliable cable. Can't beat it for the price.
